Gedde Watanabe https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Gedde_Watanabe 0 Gary "Gedde" Watanabe (born June 26, 1955) is a Japanese-American actor. He is perhaps best known for voicing the character of Ling in the 1998 successful animated film Mulan and its 2004 sequel, Mulan II as well as playing Long Duk Dong in the 1984 film Sixteen Candles.
